<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a1df0e0-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6852"><num value="6852">§ 6852.</num><heading> Interagency data standardization</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Not later than 30 months after <date date="2022-04-29">April 29, 2022</date>, the Secretaries shall jointly develop and adopt interagency standards to ensure compatibility and interoperability among applicable Federal databases with respect to the collection and dissemination of data—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a1df0e1-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6852/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> relating to recreation sites on Federal land; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a1df0e2-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6852/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> used to depict locations at which recreation uses are available to the public.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id7a1df0e3-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/117/114/s3">Pub. L. 117–114, § 3</ref>, <date date="2022-04-29">Apr. 29, 2022</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/136/1175">136 Stat. 1175</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/118/234/tIII/s354/1">Pub. L. 118–234, title III, § 354(1)</ref>, <date date="2025-01-04">Jan. 4, 2025</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/138/2917">138 Stat. 2917</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id7a1df0e4-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id7a1df0e5-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id7a1df0e6-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2025—Par. (1). <ref href="/us/pl/118/234">Pub. L. 118–234</ref> substituted “recreation sites” for “public outdoor recreational use”.</p>
</note>
</notes>
